The article is a press briefing by Press Secretary Robert Gibbs and Jared Bernstein, the Vice President's Chief Economist, discussing the roadmap to recovery outlined by President Obama and Vice President Biden. They highlight the ways in which the American Recovery and Reinvestment Act will be accelerated in its second 100 days. The goal is to create or save 600,000 jobs over this period. They also discuss 10 major projects that will be implemented, including health centers, airport and highway improvements, education jobs, veterans' medical centers, law enforcement officers, water systems, national parks, cleanup of super-fund sites, summer youth jobs, and construction and rehabilitation projects at military facilities. They emphasize the importance of the Recovery Act in creating jobs and spurring economic growth, and highlight the administration's commitment to transparency and accountability in the implementation of the plan.